Dear Sir,=20

First of all I would like to thank you for the great utility.=20

My monitor has no manual controls and Samsung's provided calibration softwa=
re
were complete disaster (100MB!!!). I've tuned the colors in Intel video dri=
ver
under Windows. However the picture was intensively bright under Linux and
Xgamma was not a solution (as it only modifies brightness). Therefore
DDCCONTROL was exactly what I needed!

Here is my environment:=20
1) IBM ThinkCentre S50
2) Intel Extreme Graphics card onboard. VGA Out.
3) Samsung SyncMaster 971P using analog connection.
4) Ubuntu 8.10

I am sending to you output of command "ddccontrol -p -c -d" from my monitor.
Please, see attached file "Samsung_SyncMaster_971P_Analog.txt".

As initially my monitor was not recognized by DDCCONTROL, I figured that I =
could
use SAM0248 file as a template, I copied it to SAM0247.xml and modified com=
ments
in the same manner. Then I restarted gddccontrol and verified that everythi=
ng
(Brightness, Contrast, Gamma, MagicBright presets, Color temperature, etc) =
are
working.=20

With my SAM0247.xml file "ddccontrol -p -c -d" produced the following outpu=
t:
"SAM0247.txt".

Thank you,
Grey






